<body>
    <h1>Legacy template fallback</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"aui-message warning shadowed information-macro">=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-warning">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>The following does not apply to siteaccesses configured with <code>legac=
y_mode: true</code></p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>When the standard view provider is not able to select an appropriate tem=
plate for a given content, <strong>the system fallbacks to the legacy kerne=
l and delegates the view selection to it</strong>.&nbsp;<span style=3D"font=
-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">This ensures that a content is always d=
isplayed and hence eases project migration from eZ Publish v4.x to v5.x</sp=
an></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;"><style type=3D"te=
xt/css">/*<![CDATA[*/
div.rbtoc1413895912884 {padding: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1413895912884 ul {list-style: disc;margin-left: 0px;}
div.rbtoc1413895912884 li {margin-left: 0px;padding-left: 0px;}

/*]]>*/</style></span></p>
<div class=3D"toc-macro rbtoc1413895912884">=20
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">=20
<li><a href=3D"#Legacytemplatefallback-Pagelayoutandmainblock">Pagelayout a=
nd main block</a>=20
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">=20
<li><a href=3D"#Legacytemplatefallback-Baselayoutforlegacyfallback">Base la=
yout for legacy fallback</a></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#Legacytemplatefallback-Blockname">Block name</a></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#Legacytemplatefallback-Modulelayout">Module layout</a>=20
<ul class=3D"toc-indentation">=20
<li><a href=3D"#Legacytemplatefallback-Displayinglegacymoduleresult">Displa=
ying legacy module result</a></li>=20
</ul> </li>=20
</ul> </li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#Legacytemplatefallback-Persistentvariable">Persistent varia=
ble</a></li>=20
<li><a href=3D"#Legacytemplatefallback-Assets">Assets</a></li>=20
</ul>=20
</div>
<br />
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"Legacytemplatefallback-Pagelayoutandmainblock">Pagelayout and mai=
n block</h2>
<p>When falling back to the legacy kernel, <strong>the old <code>content/vi=
ew</code> module is run</strong> to return the appropriate view for the giv=
en content. However, the pagelayout is not rendered as it needs to be still=
 rendered by Twig in the Symfony part, for consistency. In this regard, the=
 system uses the <strong>Decorator design pattern</strong> to include the g=
enerated view in your layout.</p>
<p>For this to work, you need to configure 2 things :</p>
<ol>
<li>Which template you want to use as a base template for legacy fallback</=
li>
<li>The name of the block to use in your layout</li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"Legacytemplatefallback-Baselayoutforlegacyfallback">Base layout f=
or legacy fallback</h3>
<p>You can configure this by setting the&nbsp;<code><strong>ezpublish_legac=
y.&lt;siteaccess_or_siteaccess_group&gt;.view_default_layout</strong></code=
> config key.</p>
<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>ezpublish/config/ezpublish.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">parameters:
    # eZ Publish 5.1+ only
    ezpublish_legacy.my_siteaccess.view_default_layout: AcmeDemoBundle::my_=
layout.html.twig</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Legacytemplatefallback-Blockname">Block name</h3>
<p>Internally when rendering the view coming from the legacy kernel, a Twig=
 template is created on the fly. This template extends the pagelayout you c=
onfigured and includes the content inside a block. The name of this block i=
s configurable as well (default is <code><strong>content</strong></code>).<=
/p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>ezpublish/config/ezpublish.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">parameters:
    ezpublish_legacy.&lt;siteaccess_or_siteaccess_group&gt;.view_default_la=
yout: AcmeDemoBundle::my_layout.html.twig
    ezpublish.content_view.content_block_name: content</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>my_layout.html.twig</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;!-- ... --&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    {% block content %}{# Content will be inserted here #}{% endblock %}
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"Legacytemplatefallback-Modulelayout">Module layout</h3>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message hint shadowed information-macro">=20
<p class=3D"title">Version compatibility</p>=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-hint">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p>The module layout setting is available from eZ Publish 5.1.</p>=20
</div>=20
</div>=20
<p><span style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;">The module layout=
 can also be defined the same way as the base layout, by setting the&nbsp;<=
/span><code style=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;"><strong>ezpubl=
ish_legacy.&lt;scope&gt;.module_default_layout</strong></code><span style=
=3D"font-size: 10.0pt;line-height: 13.0pt;"> config key. This layout is use=
d to handle &quot;non content&quot; related legacy requests.</span></p>
<h4 id=3D"Legacytemplatefallback-Displayinglegacymoduleresult">Displaying l=
egacy module result</h4>
<p>This makes your base layout reusable. However, content generated by lega=
cy modules (i.e. <code>/ezinfo/about</code>) will not be automatically inse=
rted as your layout will be rendered as a regular template, receiving <code=
>module_result</code> variable coming from the legacy kernel. The solution =
is to use 2 different templates, one for the global layout, and another for=
 legacy module rendering:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>AcmeDemoBundle::layout.html.twig</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;!-- Insert everything you need here that is common --&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    {% block content %}{# Regular content will be inserted here #}{% endblo=
ck %}
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>AcmeDemoBundle::layout_legacy.html.twig</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">{% extends &quot;AcmeDemoBundle::layout.html.twig&quot; %}
&nbsp;
{% block content %}
    {# module_result variable is received from the legacy controller. #}
    {# It holds the legacy module result #}
    {{ module_result.content|raw }}
{% endblock %}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>ezpublish/config/ezpublish.yml</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">parameters:
    ezpublish_legacy.my_siteaccess.module_default_layout: AcmeDemoBundle::l=
ayout_legacy.html.twig
    ezpublish_legacy.my_siteaccess.view_default_layout: AcmeDemoBundle::lay=
out.html.twig</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"Legacytemplatefallback-Persistentvariable">Persistent variable</h=
2>
<p>The persistent variable is a special variable in legacy templates that y=
ou can set in order to pass values from the content template to the pagelay=
out. This variable, among others, is accessible from the configured Twig pa=
gelayout thanks to the helper <code><strong>ezpublish.legacy</strong></code=
>.</p>
<p>Actually, all data <a href=3D"http://doc.ez.no/eZ-Publish/Technical-manu=
al/4.x/Templates/The-pagelayout/Variables-in-pagelayout#module_result" clas=
s=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">contained in <code>$module_result</cod=
e> in the legacy kernel</a> is exposed.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>Access to the persistent variable</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;!-- ... --&gt;
    {% if ezpublish.legacy.has( 'content_info' ) %}
        {% set persistent_variable =3D ezpublish.legacy.get( 'content_info'=
 )['persistent_variable'] %}
    {% endif %}
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    {% block content %}{# Content will be inserted here #}{% endblock %}
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"Legacytemplatefallback-Assets">Assets</h2>
<p>Like the persistent variable, it is possible to require css and/or javas=
cripts assets from a content template through the legacy <code>ezscript_req=
uire()</code> and <code>ezcss_require()</code> template operators.</p>
<p>You can easily retrieve those requested assets from the legacy template =
in the Twig pagelayout with the <code><strong>ezpublish.legacy</strong></co=
de> helper.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>Getting assets requested from a legacy template</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"theme: Eclipse; brush: php; gutter: false" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;!-- ... --&gt;
    {% set requested_css_files =3D ezpublish.legacy.get( 'css_files' ) %}
    {% set requested_js_files =3D ezpublish.legacy.get( 'js_files' ) %}
&nbsp;
    {# &quot;configured&quot; assets are the ones defined in design.ini (Fr=
ontendCSSFileList/FrontendJavaScriptList) #}
    {% set configured_js_files =3D ezpublish.legacy.get( 'js_files_configur=
ed' ) %}
    {% set configured_css_files =3D ezpublish.legacy.get( 'css_files_config=
ured' ) %}
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    {% block content %}{# Content will be inserted here #}{% endblock %}
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>=20
<div class=3D"aui-message warning shadowed information-macro">=20
<p class=3D"title">Assetic incompatibility</p>=20
<span class=3D"aui-icon icon-warning">Icon</span>=20
<div class=3D"message-content">=20
<p><strong>Warning:</strong> If you use Assetic to combine and/or compress =
your assets, please note that <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current/coo=
kbook/assetic/asset_management.html#assets" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"=
nofollow"><code>javascripts</code> and <code>stylesheets</code> Twig tags</=
a> currently don't support variable file lists, so you won't be able to use=
 them with the example above.</p>=20
</div>=20
</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
